This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommendation systems. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of neural networks and deep learning methods indicates that it could be classified under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on enhancing feature informativeness and model interpretability suggests that it could also be classified under the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
